Company Background

Our client is a leading provider of intelligent transportation systems, delivering innovative solutions such as scheduling, route optimization, staffing, asset management, and communication systems. With offices across North America, Northern Europe, Australia, and the United Kingdom, the company collaborates with public transit agencies to develop smarter and more effective public transit solutions.
Project Description

The project focuses on developing .NET Core-based microservices applications, leveraging modern infrastructure and best practices. Responsibilities include automating Azure infrastructure deployment, enhancing CI/CD pipelines, and integrating security and monitoring tools to ensure high availability and reliability.
Technologies
• Terraform
• Monitoring tools (Grafana, Prometheus, Azure App Insights, Loki)
• Networking
• Bash/PowerShell
• Invicti
What You'll Do
• Collaborate with product owners, developers, and QA to define specifications and deliver features iteratively;
• Automate deployment of Azure infrastructure for microservices applications;
• Improve and maintain CI/CD pipelines to optimize release cycles and reduce deployment time;
• Monitor system performance and troubleshoot issues to ensure reliability and scalability;
• Implement security best practices and maintain compliance with industry standards;
• Integrate with external APIs and ensure seamless functionality;
• Document infrastructure designs, deployment processes, and operational runbooks;
• Evaluate emerging tools and technologies to enhance scalability, maintainability, and efficiency;
Job Requirements
• 3+ years of experience as an Azure DevOps Engineer;
• Strong knowledge of Azure, Docker/Kubernetes (AKS), and Terraform;
• Experience with Azure DevOps Pipelines and CI/CD best practices;
• Understanding of object-oriented design and design patterns;
• Familiarity with agile development methodologies;
• Excellent communication and organizational skills;
• Level of English - from Intermediate (spoken/written);
What Do We Offer

The global benefits package includes:
• Technical and non-technical training for professional and personal growth;
• Internal conferences and meetups to learn from industry experts;
• Support and mentorship from an experienced employee to help you professional grow and development;
• Internal startup incubator;
• Health insurance;
• Sports activities to promote a healthy lifestyle;
• Flexible work options, including remote and hybrid opportunities;
• Referral program for bringing in new talent;
• Work anniversary program and additional vacation days.

